  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6815.54 sitting directly in the massive negative gamma cluster (6800-6820), dealers are aggressively buying this dip as they're short gamma and forced to hedge delta-long positions. The -73.8% GEX surge and wall break event confirms dealers just got steamrolled and are now in full hedging mode, creating strong technical support in the 6800-6820 zone. Watch for explosive moves if we break below 6800 (more dealer buying) or above 6840 where dealers flip to selling into strength.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect violent bounces off this 6800-6820 support zone as dealers buy every dip.",
